title: BOYS TENNIS: Chesaning gets pivotal victory at No. 1 singles to beat Corunna
text:
Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Jared Brown 
JARED BROWN OF CHESANING makes a return to Corunna’s No. 1 singles player Connor Svrcek Tuesday at Corunna. Brown won in three sets 6-7 (5-7), 6-4, 6-3. Chesaning won the match, 5-3. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy 
CORUNNA’S CONNOR SVRCEK makes a return to Jared Brown of Chesaning Tuesday at Corunna. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Jarrett Kelley 
JARRETT KELLEY OF CHESANING unleashes a serve in his No. 4 singles match against Corunna’s Tyler Quirk Tuesday at Corunna. Kelley won 6-2, 7-5. Chesaning defeated Corunna 5-3. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Jared Brown 
CHESANING’S NO. 1 SINGLES PLAYER Jared Brown follows through on a serve Tuesday against Corunna’s Connor Svrcek. Brown won in three sets, 6-7 (tiebreaker 5-7), 6-4, 6-3 in the last match. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Doug Thoma 
CORUNNA’S DOUG THOMA serves against No. 2 singles opponent Nick Karlik of Chesaning Tuesday at Corunna. Karlik won 6-2, 3-6, 6-2. Chesaning captured a 5-3 non-conference victory. Posted: Wednesday, September 30, 2015 11:20 am BOYS TENNIS: Chesaning gets pivotal victory at No. 1 singles to beat Corunna By JEROME MURPHY Argus-Press Sports Writer The Argus-Press | 0 comments 
CORUNNA — Chesaning extended its single-season, school-record win total to 15 Tuesday — but it needed a marathon victory at No. 1 singles to pull out a 5-3 win over Corunna.
